name: Ipupiara
description:
Also known as seaman, it is a kind of sea monster that was part of the mythology of the Tupi peoples who inhabited the coast of Brazil in the 16th century. According to popular belief, he attacked people and ate parts of their bodies. According to reports from Colonia Brazil, an Ipupiara was found and killed in the captaincy of São Vicente, in the year 1564. <Crypto Legends | A Series by Renancio Monte | 2021>
